pull_request.body: This PR is adding the field `card_type` to the billing_info creation/update process, this field was read-only but now can be sent by the merchant to specify the card type, this is useful when using a co-branded card brand like Cartes Bancaires.

pull_request.body:
## How to test
The dotnet client works differently when compared to other clients. It is not tested against fixtures but against prod environment. Unit testing is not a good option in this case.

To test these changes, refer to https://github.com/recurly/v2-playground/pull/145. I added a new script to check if the action_result field is being returned.
There's some setup needed before running the script.
* Create an account with a new billing info that uses Boleto, iDEAL or Sofort Payment methods as primary.
* On the /Library/Configuration/Settings.cs file, change `RercurlyServerUri` and `ValidDomain` values both to connect to qa environment (Eg: `"https://{0}.qa2.recurlyqa.com/v2{1}";`)
* In the new script file, change the line `var purchase = new Purchase("account_code_here", currency);` to pass your account code.
* Then run the script against QA environment, it should return a Purchase with a transaction
